  "env_id": "vlc_env@0.1",
  "description": "You are preparing a Collector's Edition USB drive containing an indie game's official soundtrack. Using the master folder at /home/ga/Music/composer_delivery/ and the draft playlist at /home/ga/Documents/draft_ost.m3u, create a distribution folder at /home/ga/Desktop/OST_Distribution/ containing a 'tracks' subfolder. Copy the 12 tracks specified in the M3U into the tracks/ folder without using symlinks. Generate a portable XSPF playlist at /home/ga/Desktop/OST_Distribution/soundtrack.xspf with the title 'Cyber-Neon: Original Soundtrack' and creator 'Neon Syndicate Games'. The XSPF must maintain the M3U sequence, use relative paths for track locations (e.g., 'tracks/filename.mp3'), and use clean song names extracted from ID3 tags for track titles.",
